Name:
    LACE 2: an R package for the inference of longitudinal cancer evolution models
Description:
    LACE is an algorithmic framework that processes single-cell somatic mutation profiles from cancer samples collected at different time points and in distinct experimental settings, to produce longitudinal models of cancer evolution. The approach solves a Boolean Matrix Factorization problem with phylogenetic constraints, by maximizing a weighed likelihood function computed on multiple time points. From the version LACE 2.0, the framework computes the longitudinal clonal tree and provides a graphical user interface to annotate, select relevant variants and explore the inferred results interactively.
